**Abstract:**
Essay dated May 24, 1993, titled "Applying Frei to my issue." The document proposes to apply Hans Frei's analysis of narrative biblical reading to the medieval period, arguing that the shift Frei describes in the 17th-18th centuries was actually a logical development of an earlier epistemological shift in the 11th-12th centuries. The author contends that the religious reading of the Bible is not a species of narrative reading but an original reading correlative to an original way of being in the world, and that the modus scientialis and modus Christianus are mutually exclusive.

**AI Recommendation:** Important methodological essay connecting Frei's hermeneutical insights to medieval theological history; key to the Chantilly project.

